          <p>(A) The core procedure of the algorithm. (B) Determination of the SSE sequence of a hit. A sequence similarity search is performed to retrieve a hit list for the query sequence. Next, for each hit protein, directly obtain its SSE sequence from the known structure or synthesize one by position-specific voting according to the homologs (Hom) of the hit retrieved by the second-round sequence similarity search against a reference protein structure dataset. An SSE transformation of the sequence alignments between the query and hits is then carried out by replacing the amino acids with SSE codes. Finally, the PSSM is generated according to the transformed alignments.</p>
